This paper is about depth estimation from images using a convolutional neural network. The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The use of transfer learning and pre-trained networks also suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves training a neural network, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The application of depth estimation could also suggest that it belongs to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the use of high-resolution depth maps and image processing techniques could suggest that it belongs to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
